Millions of people converge on Xi'an every year to learn about the city‚Äôs rich history and to see ancient artifacts, such as the famous terra-cotta army. However, the fortified wall around its old city center has always garnered attention from residents and tourists alike.&nbsp;   
The wall that surrounds Xi‚Äôan is 8.5 miles long and protects the city‚Äôs historic artifacts, including its famed terra-cotta warriors.

It‚Äôs the weekend of the mid-autumn festival in¬†Xi‚Äôan, and all roads seem to lead to the south gate of the city's wall. In China‚Äôs central province of Shaanxi, Xi‚Äôan is primarily known for the museum that houses the army of¬†terra-cotta warriors commissioned by¬†China‚Äôs first ruler¬†to protect him in his afterlife. But the wall, on this Saturday evening, is where all the action o‚Ä¶

